<h1 id="block-scoping">Block scoping</h1>
<p><code>let</code> and <code>const</code> are said to be &quot;block scoping.&quot; In JavaScript, a block is code inside <em>{ ... }</em>. These variables are only available inside their blocks.</p>
<pre><code class="language-js">if (true) {
  let a = 'hello'
}
console.log(a)  //=&gt; undefined
</code></pre>
<blockquote>
<p>â†³ <code>a</code> is only available inside the <em>if</em> block.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>There are more blocks than <code>if</code>s:</p>
<pre><code class="language-js">function greet () { /*...*/ }
if (hidden) { /*...*/ }
else { /*...*/ }
try { /*...*/ }
catch (e) { /*...*/ }
finally { /*...*/ }
switch (state) { /*...*/ }
for (;;) { /*...*/ }
while (true) { /*...*/ }
</code></pre>
